As an alternative, RBI has authorised card networks and card issuers to offer card tokenisation services, which means the replacement of actual credit and debit card details with an alternate code called \xe2\x80\x9ctoken\xe2\x80\x9d. The user can either choose to tokenise their card by giving consent for future transactions or choose to continue without tokenisation.\\n\\n__What is a token?__\\n\\nA token is generated when a user gives consent to Flipkart to tokenise their card. A token is a unique value for a combination of card, token requestor (Flipkart is a token requestor & accepts request from the customer for tokenisation of a card and passes it onto the card network to issue a corresponding token) and device. The token does not contain any personal information linked to your card and is generated only when a customer uses a new card for a successful transaction on Flipkart.\\n\\n__Is it safe to tokenise my card?__\\n\\nYes. A tokenised card transaction is considered safer as the actual card details are not shared with the Flipkart during transaction processing . Card information is stored with the authorised card networks or card issuers only and Flipkart does not store your 16-digit card number.\\n\\n__Is tokenisation of card mandatory?__\\n\\nNo, customer can choose whether or not to tokenise their card.\\n\\n__What happens if I don\xe2\x80\x99t give consent to secure my card?__\\n\\nIf you don\xe2\x80\x99t give consent to tokenise your card, you need to enter your card details for every transaction as stipulated under the RBI guidelines.","savedVpaFAQ":"__Why is my UPI being saved on Flipkart?__\\n\\nIt\'s quicker.           <h2>
           Buy Top Mobiles Under 10000 Online to Bring Home a High-end Device
          </h2>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <div>
           The market of smartphones is flooded with new models, high-end features, high-resolution cameras, and powerful processors. The good news is that the rising competition is leading to dropping of prices. Once upon a time, the
           <a href="/smartphone-mobile-store">
            smartphones
           </a>
           were considered advanced communication devices that cost a fortune. However, that scenario has drastically changed and now smartphones are a necessity that are available in different price ranges. If you are looking for a smartphone for yourself or to gift someone, then here are the latest top models of mobiles available under 10000:
          </div>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <h2>
           Samsung Galaxy On5
          </h2>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <div>
           With a leather-like back cover and a sturdy metal frame, the
           <a href="/samsung-galaxy-on5-gold-8-gb/p/itmedhx3uy3qsfks">
            Samsung Galaxy On5
           </a>
           is a compact smartphone. Thanks to its quad-core 1.3GHz processor and 1.5 GB of RAM, multitasking is easy and quick on this phone. Also, it has a 2600 mAh Li-ion Battery for uninterrupted connectivity.
          </div>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <h2>
           Samsung Galaxy On7
          </h2>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <div>
           Enjoy immersive viewing experience on the 13.97 cm (5.5) HD TFT display of this Samsung smartphone. A long-lasting 3000 mAh battery, 4G LTE network connectivity support, and a 13 MP rear camera are other attractive features of this smartphone.
          </div>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <h2>
           Moto E4 Plus
          </h2>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <div>
           A massive 5000 mAh battery, the Android Nougat 7.1.1 OS, and a powerful 1.3 GHz quad-core processor make this Motorola phone a popular device among many. This dual SIM smartphone comes with 32 GB of internal memory to store as many songs, videos, photos, and games as you want.
          </div>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <h2>
           Panasonic Eluga I5
          </h2>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <div>
           This smartphone comes with a helpful artificial intelligence system, named ARBO, to help you schedule your daily activities. This slim and stylish smartphone features a fingerprint sensor for protecting your data and for uninterrupted performance it has a 1.25 GHz quad-core processor with a 2 GB of RAM.
          </div>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <h2>
           Redmi Note 4
          </h2>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <div>
           With the
           <a href="/redmi-note-4-black-64-gb/p/itmeqe48766xqzb7">
            Redmi Note 4
           </a>
           , you get a 13.97 cm (5.5) full HD display, a metal body, a 5 MP front camera, and a powerful 4100 mAh Li-polymer Battery and much more. From an immersive gaming experience to easy multitasking, this phone offers powerful performance.
          </div>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <div>
           Apart from these smartphones, you can also check out the Samsung Galaxy J3 Pro, Redmi 4A, Moto C Plus, Asus Zenfone 4 Selfie, and the Asus Zenfone Max mobiles available under 10000.
          </div>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <h2>
           Advantages of Buying Mobiles Under 10,000 Online
          </h2>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <div>
           Online shopping sites offer lucrative deals, discounts, and offers to make your shopping experience rewarding. These sites also carry user reviews, ratings, and options to compare prices and specifications to make a well-informed decision. You can also use filters to ensure that you get want you are looking for. When it comes to payments, you can use net banking, credit or debit cards, UPI, or COD options. There is also the EMI option for an easy and hassle-free payment. Online shopping provides you the privilege to shop from your home after taking your time to select the right smartphone under 10000. If the phone is not up to your expectations, you can either return it or go for the replacement option.
          </div>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <h2>
           Top 10 Mobile Phones Under Rs 10,000
          </h2>
          <div>
           Mobile phones have become a necessity for almost everyone around us. Whether it be an owner of a factory or be it his worker, everyone needs a
           <a href="/mobiles">
            mobile
           </a>
           phone. The increasing demands for mobile phones have witnessed a huge drop in its price. If one is looking for a mobile phone, he/she has a variety of options. Even if we talk particularly about the mobile phones below the range of 10,000, the list is huge. Phones with high-quality sensors, 4G facility, excellent camera quality are now easily available under Rs. 10,000.
          </div>
          <div>
           Sometimes we look for a mobile phone and dont want our budget to exceed Rs. 10,000. So, here is the list of top 10 mobiles phones from Rs.5000 to Rs.10000 range.
          </div>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <h2>
           1. Xiaomi Redmi Note 4
          </h2>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <div>
           Redmi note 4 was launched in May 2017. This dual sim phone has a 2GHz Octa-core Qualcomm Snapdragon 625 processor and operates on Android 6.0. It comes with 32GB internal storage (expandable up to 128GB) and options of 2, 3 and 4GB RAM. It has a 13MP rear camera and a 5MP front camera. It has a price starting at Rs. 9,999 and is available in black, gold and dark gray color.
          </div>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <h2>
           2. Xiaomi Redmi 4
          </h2>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <div>
           The next place in this list is taken by another Xiaomi phone Redmi 4. Its main feature is its long lasting battery life. It was launched in May 2017 and has 2, 3 and 4GB RAM. It has 1.4GHz Octa-core Qualcomm Snapdragon 435 processor. The features are similar to the latter, but it is less powerful. It falls within Rs 9000 and is available in black and gold color.
          </div>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <h2>
           3. Yu Yureka Black
          </h2>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <div>
           This
           <a href="/yu-yureka-black-chrome-black-32-gb/p/itmeuyd7pxcy29xe">
            Yureka Black
           </a>
           is available only in black. It was launched in June 2017. It has a metallic body, with 4GB of RAM and 32GB internal memory. It has 13MP rear camera and 8MP front camera. This Android 6.0 mobile phone is available at just Rs 9000.
          </div>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <h2>
           4. Lenovo K6 Power
          </h2>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <div>
           Next in the budget category is this Lenovo phone. It was launched in may 2017 and has 13MP rear camera. It runs Android 6.0.1 OS and has 1.4 GHz Octa-core Qualcomm Snapdragon 430 processor. Its price is within Rs 10,000.
          </div>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <h2>
           5. Intex Aqua 5.5 VR
          </h2>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <div>
           If you are planning to buy a phone below Rs. 5,000
           <a href="/intex-aqua-5-5-vr-champagne-white-8-gb/p/itmenf7fx4ujfznw">
            Intex Aqua 5.5 VR
           </a>
           is the best available option. This is a dual sim phone with 5MP rear and 5MP front camera. It has 1GB RAM and 8GB internal storage. It is available in champagne and white color.
          </div>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <h2>
           6. Moto E3 Power
          </h2>
          <p>
           <br/>
          </p>
          <div>
           This phone is a decent performer provided by Motorola. It gives ample battery life to view videos and play games. It has 8MP and 5MP rear and front cameras respectively. It has 1 GHz Quad-core processor and has a price falling below Rs 8,000.
          </div>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <h2>
           7. Samsung Galaxy J3 Pro
          </h2>
          <p>
           <br/>
          </p>
          <div>
           <a href="/samsung-galaxy-j3-pro-gold-16-gb/p/itmeu35jfryetgew">
            Samsung Galaxy J3 Pro
           </a>
           phone is a perfect pick if you want to go for a brand name. It has 1.4 GHz Quad core processor. It has 8 and 5 MP rear and front cameras respectively. The price below Rs. 8,000 is its major attraction.
          </div>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <h2>
           8. Coolpad Note 5 Lite
          </h2>
          <p>
           <br/>
          </p>
          <div>
           <a href="/coolpad-note-5-lite-grey-space-grey-16-gb/p/itmetm97thvzafpg">
            Coolpad Note 5 Lite
           </a>
           phone is basically a decent looking piece in the sub-10k category. It is hard to recommend this phone over the previously mentioned pieces but its price of Rs. 7,499 is a major positive point.
          </div>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <h2>
           9. Coolpad Note 5
          </h2>
          <p>
           <br/>
          </p>
          <div>
           It is considered as a larger cousin of
           <a href="/coolpad-note-5-space-grey-32-gb/p/itmeuyd9duk8hen4">
            Coolpad note 5
           </a>
           lite. But its features are far better than the later. The best part is its battery which can last for around two days on a regular usage. Its price is below Rs 10000.
          </div>
          <div>
           <br/>
          </div>
          <h2>
           10. Lenovo Vibe K5 Plus
          </h2>
          <p>
           <br/>
          </p>
          <div>
           It has 1.7 GHz Octa-core Qualcomm Snapdragon 616 processor. The phone has a good performance. Its Android 5.1 OS is a slight disappointment. It has decent camera quality and the memory and storage features are also sufficient for a normal user.
          </div>

The Cash on Delivery payment option cannot be used to pay the balance amount.","savedCardFAQ":"__Why is my card being tokenised?__\n\nAs per the new RBI guidelines to make card data more secure, merchants like Flipkart cannot store the card details of users. As an alternative, RBI has authorised card networks and card issuers to offer card tokenisation services, which means the replacement of actual credit and debit card details with an alternate code called token. The user can either choose to tokenise their card by giving consent for future transactions or choose to continue without tokenisation.\n\n__What is a token?__\n\nA token is generated when a user gives consent to Flipkart to tokenise their card. A token is a unique value for a combination of card, token requestor (Flipkart is a token requestor & accepts request from the customer for tokenisation of a card and passes it onto the card network to issue a corresponding token) and device. The token does not contain any personal information linked to your card and is generated only when a customer uses a new card for a successful transaction on Flipkart.\n\n__Is it safe to tokenise my card?__\n\nYes. A tokenised card transaction is considered safer as the actual card details are not shared with the Flipkart during transaction processing . Card information is stored with the authorised card networks or card issuers only and Flipkart does not store your 16-digit card number.\n\n__Is tokenisation of card mandatory?__\n\nNo, customer can choose whether or not to tokenise their card.\n\n__What happens if I dont give consent to secure my card?__\n\nIf you dont give consent to tokenise your card, you need to enter your card details for every transaction as stipulated under the RBI guidelines.","savedVpaFAQ":"__Why is my UPI being saved on Flipkart?__\n\nIt's quicker.
